==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Audita querela
<hw>Au*di"ta que*re"la</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>. <ety>[L., the complaint
having been heard.]</ety> <fld>(Law)</fld> <def>A writ which lies for a
party against whom judgment is recovered, but to whom good matter of
discharge has subsequently accrued which could not have been availed of
to prevent such judgment.</def> <rj><au>Wharton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Audition</ent>⟦br⟧
